high_descs: Go forward and face the counter with the knife on your right.
Take the knife from the counter in front of you.
Turn right then face the bread on the counter to your left.
Cut the bread in front of you on the counter.
Turn around and face the cabinet under the tomato on the counter.
Open the cabinet in front of you, place the knife inside and close it.
Turn left then face the bread on the counter to your left.
Take a bread slice from the counter in front of you.
Turn right then face the microwave on the counter on your right.
Heat up the slice of bread, take the bread out and close the microwave.
Turn around and face the counter with the toaster on it.
Place the slice of bread on top of the counter in front of you.
anns.task_desc: Heat up a slice of bread in the microwave.

high_descs: Walk to the end of the kitchen and face the counter on the right
Pick up the butter knife on the counter
Turn to the right and face the loaf of bread sitting on the counter
Slice the bread in half
Turn around and face the stove and oven
Open the lower right cabinet door and place the knife inside
Turn back around and face the loaf of bread on the counter
Pick up a slice of bread on the counter
Turn to the right and walk to the microwave at the end of the counter on the left
Open the microwave and place the bread inside, warm it up then remove it
Turn around and walk to the counter with the toaster on it
Place the slice of bread on the counter next to the paper towel
anns.task_desc: Warming up a fresh slice of bread in the microwave

high_descs: Walk straight towards the window and then turn right.
Pick up the knife on the counter.
Take a step to the right.
Cut the loaf of bread on the counter into several slices.
Turn around and head towards the cabinet to the right of the oven.
Open the cabinet, place the knife inside, and close it.
Turn around to face the loaf of bread on the counter.
Pick up a slice of bread from the counter.
Turn right and head towards the microwave to your left.
Place the bread inside, heat it up, and take it back out.
Turn around and head towards the toaster on the counter.
Place the bread to the left of the paper towel.
anns.task_desc: Place a warm slice of bread to the left of the paper towel and the knife in the cabinet.

high_descs: Go forward to the end of the room. To to the right to the counter above the dishwasher.
Pick up the butter knife that is on the counter.
Move to the right so that you are in front of the loaf of bread.
Use the knife to cut the bread into slices.
Turn around and go across the room to the cupboard where the tea pot is.
Open the cupboard underneath the counter where the tea pot is, put the butter knife inside the cupboard, and close the cupboard.
Turn around and go back to the counter where the bread is.
Pick up a slice of the bread.
Go to the right until you get to the microwave, which will be on your left before the fridge.
Put the bread inside the microwave, close the door, turn it on to cook, take the bread out of the microwave and close the door.
Turn back to the left, go forward, turn to the left again and go to the counter that has the toaster on it.
Put the slice of bread on the counter to the left of the roll of paper towels.
anns.task_desc: Place a cooked slice of bread on a counter.

high_descs: Walk forward across the room then turn right to face the counter.
Pick up the knife on the counter.
Take a step to the right to face the bread on the counter.
Cut the bread on the counter into slices.
Turn around and face the right most cabinet under the counter.
Place the knife in the bottom right cabinet under the counter.
Turn around to face the bread on the counter.
Pick up a slice from the bread on the counter.
Turn right and walk to the end of the counter and face the microwave on the left.
Heat the bread slice in the microwave and remove it.
Turn around and walk forward to face the counter with paper towels on it.
Place the bread slice on the counter to the left of the paper towels.
anns.task_desc: To cut plus heat a slice of bread as well as place it on the counter by the paper towels.
